184
00:17:46,858 --> 00:17:49,539
[SPEAKER_09]: well in Medford, Everett, and 10 other cities.

185
00:17:50,340 --> 00:18:08,268
[SPEAKER_09]: And I just want to pick up on what Immigrant Learning Center said, and all these, I see all these other wonderful service agencies, but Renee from Wachling Court reminded me that one of the things that Bread of Life does is we provide grocery delivery to senior citizens.

186
00:18:08,308 --> 00:18:12,249
[SPEAKER_09]: And we just picked up Wachling Court about, I think it was one month ago.

187
00:18:13,670 --> 00:18:15,491
[SPEAKER_09]: So happy to be doing more in Medford.

188
00:18:16,502 --> 00:18:29,389
[SPEAKER_09]: We do about 850 of those deliveries a month to mainly the seniors, some elderly, disabled, and some disabled, and some COVID quarantined, if they're referred by health care.

189
00:18:30,869 --> 00:18:38,113
[SPEAKER_09]: And we're doing about 3,000 people per month at our Malden pantry, which serves the 13 cities.

190
00:18:40,385 --> 00:19:00,411
[SPEAKER_09]: doing other things as well, but just thank you for continuing to support Bread of Life and the YMCA Mississippi market and the food security, because everybody knows that, you know, the extra SNAP benefits just just ended and also people are being redetermined for Medicaid.

191
00:19:00,451 --> 00:19:07,493
[SPEAKER_09]: So there's a lot of financial shifting going on and our numbers are still very high because of those things.

192
00:19:07,753 --> 00:19:07,913
[SPEAKER_09]: And

193
00:19:09,322 --> 00:19:17,446
[SPEAKER_09]: The inflation, especially food costs, some of our costs for purchasing some of our products for like the student backpacks that we do whenever it.

194
00:19:19,187 --> 00:19:33,555
[SPEAKER_09]: Some of those have actually doubled in the past year, you know, you know, went from this 750 for a package to, you know, 15 so it's it's it's it's been brutal out there and for you know.

195
00:19:34,507 --> 00:19:38,848
[SPEAKER_09]: our seniors and other people who are on fixed income, it's very hard.

196
00:19:38,909 --> 00:19:43,270
[SPEAKER_09]: So thank you for all the city is doing for the food security.

197
00:19:43,310 --> 00:19:44,290
[SPEAKER_09]: We really appreciate it.

198
00:19:44,831 --> 00:19:48,052
