204
00:20:15,430 --> 00:20:23,714
[SPEAKER_02]: I just want to thank Medford for this grant, it really makes such a big difference for helping us keep Medford residents in their homes.

205
00:20:24,575 --> 00:20:28,557
[SPEAKER_02]: These are really difficult times, I know everyone sees the rents are going up, and

206
00:20:29,817 --> 00:20:38,962
[SPEAKER_02]: You know, everything's more expensive as Gabriella was saying, you know, some of the protections we've seen in the extra funding for rental assistance from the pandemic.

207
00:20:39,382 --> 00:20:40,323
[SPEAKER_02]: Those things are ending.

208
00:20:40,343 --> 00:20:51,129
[SPEAKER_02]: So we're concerned about this that's going to cause more people to be homeless so this funding really helps us do whatever we can to keep people in their homes and prevent them getting evicted so thank you.

209
00:20:52,049 --> 00:20:59,556
[SPEAKER_02]: for your support and for your presentation and all the other service agencies for working with us and our clients and making such a difference.

210
00:20:59,696 --> 00:21:05,060
[SPEAKER_02]: Every little bit helps for, you know, saving money on food or transportation and all helps them pay their rent.

211
00:21:05,100 --> 00:21:08,043
[SPEAKER_02]: And so it's really the whole community I appreciate.

212
00:21:08,263 --> 00:21:09,464
[SPEAKER_02]: So thank everyone for being here.

213
00:21:09,484 --> 00:21:13,047
[SPEAKER_11]: Great, thank you.

